## 6. Gap Analysis — What the MVP Covers vs What It Cannot

| Requirement | MVP Covered? | Gap | Solution |
|---|---|---|---|
| Login Events (IP + Geo) | ✅ Yes | None | DfCA covers this fully |
| Failed / Successful Logins | ✅ Yes | None | Via Login History logs |
| Fast Travel / Impossible Travel | ✅ Yes | None | Built-in DfCA policy |
| Suspicious IP | ✅ Yes | None | Threat intelligence in DfCA |
| Breakglass Account Use | ⚠️ Partial | No real-time alert by default | Custom policy required |
| Multiple Failed Logins | ✅ Yes | None | Built-in brute force policy |
| Session Hijacking Detection | ⚠️ Partial | Limited without Shield | Shield Event Monitoring adds session tracking |
| Suspicious User Agent | ⚠️ Partial | Manual filter setup required | Custom activity policy needed |
| Data / File Export Detection | ✅ Yes | None | Event Log Files cover this |
| Bulk API Data Request | ⚠️ Partial | Threshold tuning needed | Custom policy + threshold config |
| Bulk Deletion Operations | ⚠️ Partial | Custom policy needed | Activity policy with count filter |
| Field-level Access Events | ❌ No | ELF does not capture field views | Requires Salesforce Shield |
| New Account Creation Alert | ✅ Yes | None | Setup Audit Trail via DfCA |
| Permission Modifications | ✅ Yes | None | Setup Audit Trail covers this |
| MFA Disabled Event | ⚠️ Partial | Custom policy needed | Map to Setup Audit Trail entry |
| Audit Logging Disabled | ⚠️ Partial | Custom policy needed | Setup Audit Trail entry exists |
| Data Masking Changes | ⚠️ Partial | Custom policy needed | Shield adds more granularity |
| Access Control Setting Changes | ✅ Yes | None | Setup Audit Trail covers sharing/OWD changes |

